results.description_original:
Understand the key data privacy and cybersecurity developments that you need to know about from around the globe, and what they mean for your organization in our new podcast series, Dentons' Privacy Pod.

Hear from Dentons' market-leading global Privacy and Cybersecurity group with direct, bite-size insights on how to keep on top of the latest developments in law, the most recent regulatory enforcement actions, and emerging trends and risks. 

Our first podcast is focused on Schrems II, one of the most highly-anticipated data protection judgments in recent times and what it means for the future of the free movement of digital data around the globe.

Future podcasts will cover topics such as the increasing emergence of privacy and cyber litigation risks and how to manage them; the latest industry models for managing global data protection compliance risk; and key cyber considerations.

For more content from our global Privacy and Cybersecurity group, please visit our Privacy and Cybersecurity Law Blog which provides the latest coverage and commentary on developments in data protection.
